article.headline: Northeastern 65, Towson 55
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Bennet Davis scored 23 points and had 13 rebounds and Bobby Kelly had a career-high 25 points to lead Northeastern to a 65-55 win over Towson on Wednesday night. It was Davis' third double-double of the season. Davis and Kelly dominated early for Northeastern, scoring 31 of the Huskies' 35 first-half points. Davis nearly had a double-double at the break with 17 points and nine rebounds while Kelly had 14 points. The Huskies (8-17, 6-8 Colonial Athletic Association) used a 12-0 run to help open up a 35-26 lead at halftime. NU led by as many as 14 points in the opening half. Towson (12-13, 6-8 CAA), led by Gary Neal's game-high 26 points, stormed back in the second half and got within one point several times but never drew even. When Towson closed the gap to 51-50, NU answered with a Kelly 3-pointer and two Davis free throws to push the lead back to 6 with 4:02. From that point on, the Huskies never led by less than three points. Dennard Abraham added 12 points and eight rebounds for Towson.
